        <h1>LeetCode 3577: Minimum Cost to Make Arrays Identical (C++)</h1>

        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                You are given two integer arrays arr and brr of the same length, and an integer k. You can perform the following operation any number of times: Select an index i where 0 &lt;= i &lt; arr.length, and update arr[i] to any integer value. Each operation has a cost equal to abs(arr[i] - brr[i]) * k. Return the minimum total cost to make arr identical to brr after performing some operations.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: arr = [1,2,3,4], brr = [2,3,4,5], k = 1<br/>
                Output: 4<br/>
                Explanation: Change arr to [2,3,4,5] with total cost = |1-2|*1 + |2-3|*1 + |3-4|*1 + |4-5|*1 = 4.<br/><br/>
                Input: arr = [10,20,30], brr = [10,20,30], k = 5<br/>
                Output: 0<br/>
                Explanation: Arrays are already identical, so no operations are needed.<br/><br/>
                Input: arr = [5,10], brr = [10,5], k = 2<br/>
                Output: 10<br/>
                Explanation: Change arr[0] to 10 and arr[1] to 5 with total cost = |5-10|*2 + |10-5|*2 = 20. However, we can swap positions for a cost of 10.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    long long minCost(vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; arr, vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; brr, long long k) {
        int n = arr.size();
        long long directCost = 0;
        
        // Calculate direct cost of making each element identical
        for (int i = 0; i &lt; n; i++) {
            directCost += (long long)abs(arr[i] - brr[i]) * k;
        }
        
        // Calculate swap cost using optimal assignment
        vector&lt;int&gt; sortedArr = arr;
        vector&lt;int&gt; sortedBrr = brr;
        sort(sortedArr.begin(), sortedArr.end());
        sort(sortedBrr.begin(), sortedBrr.end());
        
        long long swapCost = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i &lt; n; i++) {
            swapCost += (long long)abs(sortedArr[i] - sortedBrr[i]) * k;
        }
        
        return min(directCost, swapCost);
    }
};</code></pre>
